rComments: Engaging and well spoken prof! Interesting concepts were taught. The difficulty in this course is in the amount of readings but he breaks them down very thoroughly during lecture. Office hours are very informative and he's reasonable with extensions, provided it's not last minute. I'd advise lecture over readings but do try and keep up with them.

rComments: Amazing prof, well spoken! Cares about the students and course material. Lectures are actually a pleasure to attend. Readings are fun to read even if they are difficult at times and are well explained in lecture. Would take this course again!

Uses interesting readings along with documentaries (in class) to engage students in content. Presents all arguments with balanced critiques in unbiased manner, despite his initial warning of him being a Foucaultian anthropologist. More anthropological readings than other social sciences, but I enjoyed it nevertheless. Easy, great course.
Great teacher. He is funny, engaging and thorough.
